#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.170"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.170:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.170:0.2"
msgid "17. Āghātavagga "
msgstr "17. Resentment "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.170:0.3"
msgid "170. Bhaddajisutta "
msgstr "170. With Bhaddaji "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.202, sc1
msgctxt "an5.170:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

msgctxt "an5.170:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā bhaddaji yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Bhaddaji went up to Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "an5.170:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ bhaddajiṃ āyasmā ānando etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and Venerable Ānanda said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.170:1.4"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso bhaddaji, dassanānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ savanānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ sukhānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ saññānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ bhavānaṃ aggan”ti? "
msgstr "“Reverend Bhaddaji, what is the best sight, the best sound, the best happiness, the best perception, and the best state of existence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.170:2.1"
msgid "“Atthāvuso, brahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī, yo taṃ brahmānaṃ passati, idaṃ dassanānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend, there is this Brahmā, the undefeated, the champion, the universal seer, the wielder of power. When you see Brahmā, that’s the best sight. "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.2"
msgid "Atthāvuso, ābhassarā nāma devā sukhena abhisannā parisannā. "
msgstr "There are the gods called ‘of streaming radiance’, who are drenched and steeped in pleasure. "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.3"
msgid "Te kadāci karahaci udānaṃ udānenti: "
msgstr "Every so often they feel inspired to exclaim: "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.4"
msgid "‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh, what bliss! Oh, what bliss!’ "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.5"
msgid "Yo taṃ saddaṃ suṇāti, idaṃ savanānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "When you hear that, it’s the best sound. "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.6"
msgid "Atthāvuso, subhakiṇhā nāma devā. "
msgstr "There are the gods called ‘replete with glory’. "

# NOTE: The same phrase occurs in DN 33. there, however, the line is preced with Santāvuso, sattā sukhena abhisannā parisannā paripūrā paripphuṭā, where santa obviously means “exist”. The idiom santaṃyeva usually means “actually is, in fact”.
msgctxt "an5.170:2.7"
msgid "Te santaṃyeva tusitā sukhaṃ paṭivedenti, idaṃ sukhānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "Since they’re truly content, they experience pleasure. This is the best happiness. "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.8"
msgid "Atthāvuso, ākiñcaññāyatanūpagā devā, idaṃ saññānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "There are the gods reborn in the dimension of nothingness. This is the best perception. "

msgctxt "an5.170:2.9"
msgid "Atthāvuso, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagā devā, idaṃ bhavānaṃ aggan”ti. "
msgstr "There are the gods reborn in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. This is the best state of existence.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.170:2.10"
msgid "“Sameti kho idaṃ āyasmato bhaddajissa, yadidaṃ bahunā janenā”ti? "
msgstr "“So, Venerable Bhaddaji, do you agree with what most people say about this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.170:3.1"
msgid "“Āyasmā kho ānando bahussuto. "
msgstr "“Well, Venerable Ānanda, you’re very learned. "

msgctxt "an5.170:3.2"
msgid "Paṭibhātu āyasmantaṃyeva ānandan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t you clarify this yourself?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.170:3.3"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso bhaddaji, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Reverend Bhaddaji, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.170:3.4"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā bhaddaji āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” Bhaddaji replied. "

msgctxt "an5.170:3.5"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando etadavoca: "
msgstr "Ānanda said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.170:4.1"
msgid "“Yathā passato kho, āvuso, anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ dassanānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "“What you see when the defilements end in the present life is the best sight. "

msgctxt "an5.170:4.2"
msgid "Yathā suṇato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ savanānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "What you hear when the defilements end in the present life is the best sound. "

msgctxt "an5.170:4.3"
msgid "Yathā sukhitassa anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ sukhānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "The happiness you feel when the defilements end in the present life is the best happiness. "

msgctxt "an5.170:4.4"
msgid "Yathā saññissa anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ saññānaṃ aggaṃ. "
msgstr "What you perceive when the defilements end in the present life is the best perception. "

msgctxt "an5.170:4.5"
msgid "Yathā bhūtassa anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ bhavānaṃ aggan”ti. "
msgstr "The state of existence in which the defilements end in the present life is the best state of existence.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.170:4.6"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.170:4.7"
msgid "Āghātavaggo dutiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.170:5.1"
msgid "Dve āghātavinayā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.170:5.2"
msgid "sākacchā sājīvato pañhaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.170:5.3"
msgid "Pucchā nirodho codanā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.170:5.4"
msgid "sīlaṃ nisanti bhaddajīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
